videos.description: West Virginia QB Will Grier finds WR David Sills V in stride who just gets the ball into the end zone before his knee touches the ground.
videos.headline: Sills just gets across goal line for early score

videos.description: Oklahoma QB Kyler Murray keeps it himself, finds the open hole and speeds 55 yards into the end zone for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Murray finds space for 55-yard TD run

videos.description: West Virginia RB Martell Pettaway takes the handoff, sides steps behind a block and walks into the end zone for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Pettaway waltzes in for the score

videos.description: Oklahoma QB Kyler Murray has all the time standing in the pocket and then tosses a 25-yard TD strike to WR Marquise Brown.
videos.headline: Murray has all day to find Brown for TD

videos.description: West Virginia WR Marcus Simms takes a hard hit forcing him to leave the game. Later on, he is told he done for the game and is visibly upset.
videos.headline: Mountaineers' Simms furious for not being allowed to play

videos.description: Okahoma RB Trey Sermon takes the handoff and powers into the end zone for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Sermon pounds it in for the score

videos.description: West Virginia QB Will Grier lobs a pass into the end zone to WR David Sills V, who makes a leaping catch and gets one foot down for the score.
videos.headline: Sills makes leaping TD catch

videos.description: Oklahoma RB Kennedy Brooks finds the hole and burst 68 yards downfield and into the end zone for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Brooks breaks free for 68-yard TD run

videos.description: Oklahoma QB Kyler Murray finds Marquise Brown for 65 yards, who is tackled just before the goal line and his cousin, Antonio Brown can't believe it.
videos.headline: Antonio Brown can't believe his cousin didn't score

videos.description: Oklahoma LB Caleb Kelly storms in to sack Will Grier and forces him to fumble. Kelly scoops it up and runs in for the score.
videos.headline: Kelly comes up with scoop-and-score after sack fumble

videos.description: Will Grier's pass to Dominique Maiden looks to be intercepted by Oklahoma's Tre Norwood, but Maiden wrestles it away in midair for the catch.
videos.headline: Maiden wrestles ball away from defender for big catch

videos.description: West Virginia QB Will Grier lobs a pass to WR Gary Jennings Jr. who catches it in stride and walks into the end zone for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Grier finds Jennings in stride for 57-yard TD

videos.description: West Virginia QB Will Grier takes the snap, rushes into a pile and his tight end Trevon Wesco helps push him across the goal line for the score.
videos.headline: Grier gets a push for the TD

videos.description: West Virginia QB Will Grier throws it to Gary Jennings Jr. who speeds into the end zone on a 75-yard touchdown play.
videos.headline: Grier connects with Jennings again for long TD

videos.description: On 4th-and-goal, Oklahoma QB Kyler Murray finds a wide-open Grant Calcaterra in the end zone for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Calcaterra left open for Oklahoma TD

videos.description: West Virginia QB Will Grier takes a hit and fumbles the ball. Oklahoma LB Curtis Bolton scoops it up and returns it 48 yards for the TD.
videos.headline: Bolton's scoop-and-score extends Oklahoma's lead

videos.description: West Virginia RB Martell Pettaway takes the handoff and finds his way in for the touchdown, cutting the Mountaineers' deficit to 59-56 vs. Oklahoma.
videos.headline: Pettaway weaves his way in for the TD

videos.description: On 4th-and-5, Oklahoma QB Kyler Murray has a lot of time to find CeeDee Lamb, who makes a sliding catch for the first down.
videos.headline: Murray finds Lamb on crucial 4th down conversion

videos.description: Oklahoma QB Kyler Murray reacts to his team's win over West Virginia and what to expect in the Big 12 championship vs Texas.
videos.headline: Murray says Oklahoma's defense came up big in win

videos.description: Will Grier throws for 539 yards and accounts for five total TDs, but Kyler Murray and the Oklahoma Sooners come out on top 59-56.
